# TripSync Database Schema Documentation

This document provides a detailed breakdown of the database schema for the TripSync application. The system is built using Flask-SQLAlchemy and manages users, trips, collaborative options (stays/activities), and a comprehensive expense-splitting system.

## Schema Overview

The database consists of 9 main tables categorized into four functional modules:
1. **User Management**: `users`
2. **Trip Management**: `trips`, `trip_members`
3. **Collaboration Hub**: `stay_options`, `votes`
4. **Expense Management**: `expenses`, `expense_splits`, `expense_comments`, `expense_activities`

---

## 1. User Management

### `users` table
Stores core user profile and authentication information.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `email` | String(120) | Unique identifier, indexed |
| `password_hash` | String(256) | Scrypted password hash |
| `name` | String(100) | User's display name |
| `created_at` | DateTime | Account creation timestamp |

---

## 2. Trip Management

### `trips` table
Stores the main trip entity.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `name` | String(200) | Name of the trip |
| `start_date` | Date | Official start date |
| `end_date` | Date | Official end date |
| `invite_code` | String(32) | Unique URL-safe token for joining, indexed |
| `created_by` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` (Creator) |
| `created_at` | DateTime | Trip creation timestamp |
| `google_maps_url` | String(500) | Optional link to destination maps |
| `default_currency` | String(3) | Base currency for the trip (e.g., 'USD') |

### `trip_members` table
Manages user access to trips and their specific roles.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `trip_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `trips.id` |
| `user_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` |
| `role` | String(20) | User's role: 'owner' or 'member' |
| `status` | String(20) | 'pending', 'approved', or 'rejected' |
| `joined_at` | DateTime | Timestamp when the user joined the trip |

---

## 3. Collaboration Hub (Options & Votes)

### `stay_options` table
Stores potential stays and activities for group comparison.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `trip_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `trips.id` |
| `title` | String(200) | Name of the stay or activity |
| [link](file:///c:/Users/test/Desktop/tripsync/Backend/app/routes/options.py#491-526) | String(500) | External URL (Airbnb, Booking.com, etc.) |
| `price` | Numeric(10,2) | Base price entered by user |
| `notes` | Text | Additional descriptions |
| `added_by` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` |
| `check_in_date` | Date | Start date of stay/activity |
| `check_out_date` | Date | End date (nullable if single day) |
| `category` | String(50) | 'stay' or 'activity' |
| `is_finalized` | Boolean | Selection status (Admin pick) |
| `is_per_person` | Boolean | Whether price is per person |
| `is_per_night` | Boolean | Whether price is per night |
| `image_path` | String(500) | Local path to uploaded images |
| `image_url` | String(500) | External image links (scraped) |

### `votes` table
Tracks user preferences for the generated options.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `option_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `stay_options.id` |
| `user_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` |
| `score` | Integer | 1 for a like, 0 for removed |
| `created_at` | DateTime | Vote timestamp |

---

## 4. Expense Management

### `expenses` table
Main transaction record for trip expenditures.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `trip_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `trips.id` |
| `paid_by` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` (Payer) |
| `amount` | Numeric(10,2) | Final amount in trip's default currency |
| `base_amount` | Numeric(10,2) | Original amount in transactional currency |
| `currency` | String(3) | Currency used at payment |
| `exchange_rate` | Numeric(10,4) | Rate at time of transaction |
| `description` | String(300) | Usage context (e.g., 'Lunch') |
| `category` | String(50) | 'food', 'transport', 'housing', etc. |
| `split_type` | String(20) | 'equally', 'shares', 'exact', 'percentage' |
| `expense_date` | Date | When the expense occurred |

### `expense_splits` table
Determines the breakdown of liability for each expense.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `expense_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `expenses.id` |
| `user_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` |
| `amount` | Numeric(10,2) | Exact amount owed by this user |
| `share_count` | Integer | Weight for 'shares' split type |
| `percentage` | Numeric(5,2) | Weight for 'percentage' split type |

### `expense_comments` table
Allows communication within specific transactions.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `expense_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `expenses.id` |
| `user_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `users.id` |
| `content` | Text | The comment text |

### `expense_activities` table
Audit log tracking the lifecycle of an expense.
| Column | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | Integer | Primary Key |
| `expense_id` | Integer | Foreign Key to `expenses.id` |
| `user_id` | Integer | User who triggered the activity |
| `activity_type` | String(50) | 'created', 'updated', 'comment_added' |
| `details` | String(500) | Description of the specific change |
